# Operational Security Systems & Analytics – GE HealthCare

## Overview

Supported operational security systems and built analytics tools in a regulated healthcare environment, focusing on device integrity, risk visibility, and automation of decision-support workflows.

---

## Security Platform Administration – Device Hardening & Lifecycle Support

Worked within a security device management platform to support camera and endpoint integrity across distributed sites.

* Rotated credentials and enforced password hygiene policies across managed camera devices
* Executed firmware upgrades to ensure devices remained compliant and secure
* Onboarded new cameras and network-connected devices into the management platform
* Hardened device configurations by applying security best practices and disabling unnecessary services
* Deployed and managed monitoring agents to ensure continuous device visibility and compliance
* Validated device status and configuration changes to maintain operational continuity

**Engineering Focus:**

* Device lifecycle management
* Configuration control
* Firmware validation
* Networked device security
* Operational reliability

---

## Security Risk Scoring & Decision Support Application (Python + Streamlit)

Designed and implemented a multi-factor risk scoring application to support Regional Security Directors in prioritizing response actions for upcoming events.

* Developed a weighted risk model incorporating event attributes, site exposure, operational factors, and environmental conditions
* Calculated dynamic risk scores based on multiple contributing inputs
* Identified and displayed top risk drivers to improve transparency of scoring logic
* Generated recommended mitigation actions aligned to risk thresholds
* Built an interactive web application using **Python and Streamlit** to visualize scores, drivers, and recommended actions in real time
* Structured the system to allow additional data inputs and model tuning

**Engineering Focus:**

* Systems modeling
* Risk quantification
* Multi-variable weighting logic
* Decision-support system design
* Lightweight application development

---

## Automated Operational Reporting – Power BI + Python Integration

Developed automated reporting workflows to improve visibility and eliminate manual tracking.

* Designed Power BI dashboards to visualize operational metrics and site-level performance indicators
* Built a Python “watchdog” script to monitor a designated directory for newly generated Excel files
* Implemented logic to automatically detect the latest file and ensure Power BI connected to the most recent dataset
* Reduced manual file updates and minimized risk of outdated reporting inputs
* Structured reporting models for consistent refresh behavior and stakeholder clarity

**Engineering Focus:**

* Workflow automation
* Data pipeline monitoring
* Process reliability
* Requirements translation into reporting architecture

---
